ality, the ontological difference, the turn (Kehre), the event (Ereignis), the fourfold (Geviert), and the analysis of modern technology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aFirst philosophy. 0aMetaphysics. 0aOne (The One in philosophy) 0aOne (The One in philosophy). 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Heidegger. 4aPhilosophy : History of Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Phenomenology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Phenomenology.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845650840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438456508423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438456508/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles